                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.796/21: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hibbard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-10-28T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >October 28, 1942—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>280. Your 361, October 24, 9 p.m. The War Department has not agreed to the
                    proposed use of Roberts Field by BOAC land planes and is taking up the matter
                    with representatives of British Air Ministry.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
